snippet: The flight landed at a general aviation field with no control tower — seven miles north of the Branson Airport where it was supposed to be.
abstract: Federal safety officials are investigating why Southwest Airlines plane landed at wrong airport near Branson, Mo, a general aviation field with no control tower; it was supposed to land seven miles away at Branson Airport; no one was injured.
lead_paragraph: The flight landed at a general aviation field with no control tower — seven miles north of the Branson Airport where it was supposed to be.

headline.main: Inquiry Begins Into Airliner That Landed in Wrong Place
headline.print_headline: Inquiry Begins Into Airliner That Landed in Wrong Place
